or</span><hr size=1> Bards &gt; All.  All you shamans and all you enchanter who think you are so hard, soloing easy, non-caster dragons in WW, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> BEAT THIS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>As soon as I found out that Tantor didn't summon when damaged I knew I had a new mission.  Time to put the bardic beat-down on this shaggy monster.  I quickly found that a lvl 60 bard cannot get any damage songs to land so plan B was put into effect.  Charm kite the bugger!<br><br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=12865.topic">An attempt</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> a few days ago proved to be less than successful, mainly because some weird agro features in WW resulted in two of the roaming named dragons jumping on him.  While amusing to watch, it did mean I didn't get my elephant steaks.  But today, after the patch, he was up again, and I decided to go for him.<br><br>It all started out simply enough.  I grabbed a few glacier mastodons and hurled them his way.  And then the unfortunate happened.  Cargalia wandered by and decided to join in the fight.<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.sff.net/people/fox/EQPics/Tantor/CargVsTantor.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.sff.net/people/fox/EQPics/Tantor/CargVsTantor2.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>Well, one dragon isn't really a match for a lvl 63-64, rampaging elephant from hell so I just sat back, wondered how much Tantor's HP would be reduced and waited for Cargalia to die and vape.<br><br>But it didn't happen quite like that.<br><br>Next thing I knew...<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.sff.net/people/fox/EQPics/Tantor/DeadCarg.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>As you can see, I was a bit...surprised.<br><br>Well, Carg had given his life for the cause, had given me a pair of Peerless Dragonhorn Boots and had wiped out about 45% of Tantor's health.  Things were already looking good.<br><br>But I was running out of mobs.  The Mastodons and Velium Hounds had just about had enough of this game and were hiding.  I started running around the zone with Skippy the Wonder Elephant on my arse desperately looking for mobs.  I'd taken Tantor down to 5% health by the time I reached the far side of the ToV gorge.<br><br>And ran smack into Zil Sapara.<br><br>Zil started wailing on Tantor like there was no tomorrow.  Things were looking bad and, again I fully expected my elephant's body to vape.  But to my surprise and joy...<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.sff.net/people/fox/EQPics/Tantor/DeadTantor.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>So there we have it.  Two dead mobs in the space of 45 minutes at the cost of two bubs of bard mana!  All you bards out there, grab hold of your hard hats now because we're about to get beaten senseless with the nerf stick. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24811">Trewayn Fifate</A>, <font size=1><EM>Virtuoso, master artisan and all round good egg</EM><br><a href="http://nmcs.com/kingscourt"><b>King's Court</b></a>, <a href="http://www.drinal.com">Drinal</a><p><table border=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=40%><tr><td width=15%></td><td width=10%><td width=15%></td><td width=10%><td width=15%></td><td width=10%></tr><tr><td><b>Tailoring</b></td><td><b>211</b></td><td>Fishing</td><td>199</td><td>Pottery</td><td>170</td></tr><tr><td>Baking</td><td>157</td><td>Smithing</td><td>135</td><td>Fletching</td><td>181</td></tr><tr><td>Brewing</td><td>187</td><td>Jewelry</td><td>170</td><td>Drunkard</td><td>200</td></tr></table></